author: Written by: Sam Winstrom, Assignment Editor
title: Slidell police respond to profane graffiti with arrest warrant
text:
SLIDELL, LA (WVUE) - Slidell Police have a message for an amateur graffiti artist: You might want to watch where you write "F#@K POLICE."
Dustin Carter, 27, allegedly carved an uncensored version of "F#@K POLICE" into a court house bench. Now, he's wanted for Criminal Damage to Property.
Police issued an arrest warrant along with a lesson on free speech for Carter. "Although we don't appreciate your opinion of us, you are entitled to free speech," a release by the department said. "However, defacing a court house is not acceptable."
Anyone who knows Dustin Carter's whereabouts is asked to contact the Slidell Police Department through their Facebook page, app, or by calling 985-643-3131.
